    "Management": {
      "text": "Optimal management remains unclear\nSome case reports found improvement with\ntopical\nnitroglycerin\nbrachial plexus nerve block\nelevation, heat application, soft tissue massage\nConsider vascular or hand consult if digital or skin necrosis suspected\nAnticoagulation is occasionally started (no clear evidence that it is effective)\n[3]",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "nitroglycerin",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Nitroglycerin"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "Given possibility of severe outcomes, recommend 24 hours of observation in asymptomatic patients",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
